## Security Rules
{{#PRIVATE_DIRS}}
- `{{DIR}}/` is PRIVATE. Contents must never appear in any agent output, summary, or artifact.
{{/PRIVATE_DIRS}}
- NEVER include financial account numbers, SSNs, or EINs in any output.
- NEVER commit `.env`, credentials, or API keys to any repository.

## Global Conventions
- Every project folder gets a CLAUDE.md
- xlwings for ALL xlsx writes (openpyxl destroys charts/comments)
- Session state files: current facts only, archive history when > 100 lines
- All plans follow checkbox tracking for session recovery
- ALWAYS provide the full absolute path when referencing any file in output

## MCP Servers
- desktop-commander: filesystem + process management
- memory: persistent knowledge graph
- pdf-reader: parallel PDF extraction
- context7: version-specific library docs

## Plan Standards
All plans must include: checkbox tracking for session recovery, per-step verification,
prerequisite checks, idempotent steps, failure handling with fallbacks, phase grouping,
recovery notes section, and time estimates.

## Agent Architecture
- Universal agents at `~/.claude/agents/`
- Project-specific agents at `<project>/.claude/agents/` where needed
- CLAUDE.md hierarchy is the shared-conventions backbone (walks up from CWD)
